IMO, a negative value is not counter-intuitive, we can use negative multiplier in RamWeigher and MetricsWeigher in order to control nova-scheduler behavior. Like this:

RamFilter:

"""Hosts are then weighted and sorted with the largest weight winning. If the multiplier is negative, the host with less RAM available will win (useful for stacking hosts, instead of spreading)."""

In this case, a negative value just means a preference to choose light workload hosts, and in other use case, we also can use positive value to choose heavy workload hosts to boot instance, it's just a default value.

BP spec can be found in whiteboard: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/io-ops-weight, bp spec had been merged and core reviewers had reviewed it. Doc team will draft document about io ops weighter follow the spec, so I think I should keep spec and code are consistence.'}, {'account_id': 91, 'date': '2014-08-14 14:01:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

commit_message:
Create Nova Scheduler IO Ops Weighter

Add a new nova scheduler weighter, sort the filter
hosts according to host io ops number, aims to
booting instances on light workload hosts.

DocImpact: Adds io_ops_weight_multiplier to [DEFAULT]
group of nova.conf and an new default schedule weigher.
Change-Id: Ib3c9184f10b2ebe6b1230365a51b5542dffd447c
Implements: blueprint io-ops-weight

commit_message:
Set Tempest storage protocol and vendor w/o setting driver

Set TEMPEST_STORAGE_PROTOCOL and TEMPEST_VOLUME_VENDOR if
they are changed from their defaults, or if
TEMPEST_VOLUME_DRIVER is changed.

This maintains the current behavior of setting these options if
TEMPEST_VOLUME_DRIVER is set to something other than "default".

Change-Id: I1fb7f5db0446f97de48b97a6f451882cc51c51a4

commit_message:
Enforce requirements check only for registered projects

Per documentation and discussion on mailing list, we should fail
requirements check only if the project is listed in projects.txt.
Any projects not in projects.txt are free to use libraries not
listed in global requirements file.

Change-Id: Ie1aad34585a8728ace4f7ba1cf365210449e8e1c

commit_message:
Replace admin@example.org with admin@localhost

Fuel configures account under Admin/Identity Panel/Users
with email address of admin@example.org.  To prevent
sending unwarranted messages to admin.org domain,
replacing that with admin@localhost.

Change-Id: I2cc13f64ce16ceb8913b328c9183ab91722c4c48
Closes-Bug: 1372336

commit_message:
Fix 'resume' behaivour

On KVM environments, domain property 'state' is a function that
returns a list like this: domain.state() = [3, 1]

This patch needs to be tested on VBOX environment before merging.

Change-Id: I610f6ef042d0e246b875d83188e382781995e737
Closes-Bug: #1383642

commit_message:
Removed hardcoded IDs from "node" test resources

Test resources are generated using certain helper methods to provide
key/value data. These methods hardcode ID fields which map to primary
key in the database. Subsequent creates on these resources force the
database to assign hardcoded primary keys, ignoring DB's internal
mechanisms. Though unlikely, this could lead to primary key conflicts.

This commit removes hardcoded IDs from node resources.

Change-Id: I29db29516a0a5bb00fa656c96c72636767d24bc6
Partial-Bug: #1268589

Hide the "Host Aggregates" admin panel if not enabled

access to the panel (hiding it) if not.

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-10-16 21:52:05.000000000', 'message': "Remove hardcoded IDs - possible alternative (DO NOT MERGE)

Dmitry, I made these changes on top of your patch. It seemed like the
easiest way to show you an alternative that makes more sense to me.

Adding the 'ignored_fields' parameter generalizes things and adds more
flexibility, except that I honestly don't see why we'd need that flexibility.

It seems to me that the problem stems from test.db.utils.get_test_node()
being used for two different purposes:
1. to reflect a node that was added to the DB. In this case, it needs an id
2. to contain node information to be used to create a node. When creating
   a node (ie adding to the DB), the idea is to let the DB assign the
   id value, unless the id value is explicitly passed when calling
   test.db.utils.create_test_node().

So this change basically leaves .get_test_node() alone, but where it is
used to get info for creating a node, the hard-coded id is not used (and
hence deleted).

Change-Id: I6ed15b51cc247c599addbe7098d08f8ba5f4d66b
"}]
commit_message:
Remove hardcoded IDs - possible alternative (DO NOT MERGE)

Dmitry, I made these changes on top of your patch. It seemed like the
easiest way to show you an alternative that makes more sense to me.

Adding the 'ignored_fields' parameter generalizes things and adds more
flexibility, except that I honestly don't see why we'd need that flexibility.

It seems to me that the problem stems from test.db.utils.get_test_node()
being used for two different purposes:
1. to reflect a node that was added to the DB. In this case, it needs an id
2. to contain node information to be used to create a node. When creating
   a node (ie adding to the DB), the idea is to let the DB assign the
   id value, unless the id value is explicitly passed when calling
   test.db.utils.create_test_node().

So this change basically leaves .get_test_node() alone, but where it is
used to get info for creating a node, the hard-coded id is not used (and
hence deleted).

Change-Id: I6ed15b51cc247c599addbe7098d08f8ba5f4d66b

commit_message:
Restart DHCP only when needed

Instead of an unhandled exception causing the restart of every dnsmasq
process on a system, instead restart only processes that are tied to the
network that had an operation that threw an exception.

Change-Id: Ide80cea5126ad0d8f4e47a011582198801f15fae

    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a

commit_message:
Configure glance_api_insecure and glance_api_servers

This change adds some attributes into the cookbook so
that they are configurable. They are mainly to configure
for glance_api_insecure and make glance_api_servers to be
prefixed with scheme(http or https).

Change-Id: I79e04b47918fe1ec0b45472bd2cec9afa73d5897
Closes-Bug: #1383619

commit_message:
Add 'dbshell' argument to manage.py

This command is useful when one wants to quickly get into the database.
This is basically a copied version of Django's dbshell command for PostgreSQL.

DocImpact
Change-Id: I731864f943ae1293b93efa422e6de072fe342c0e

commit_message:
Making Bandit into an installable package and adding tox tests

This large change makes bandit into an installable packahge, needed
for tox testing. I have added the tox testing scaffolding but no
real tests, they will come in a later change. I have also disabled
all failing PEP8 test (lots) since I have changed enough stuff for
one patch. I'll start re-enabling and fixing PEP8 stuff soon.

Change-Id: I774ed9149f285e4e2bceacda0484a7e2a934a3aa

commit_message:
Store image disk_format and container_format

Store the disk_format and container_format image properties so that the
agent module can pick different image writing utilties based on the
image type that is downloaded

Change-Id: I1f4064a62995ecb8d1202c071f1153ce4e97fc4e

commit_message:
Remove superfluous except/re-raise

This exception code catches all exceptions, and then always raises them
again.

More interestingly, it uses excutils.save_and_reraise_exception
incorrectly (outside a `with` statement), which triggers the pylint test
designed to catch exactly this.

Change-Id: Iab9d69944cbae5257682ac65ff2b8fba3ef7017e

commit_message:
Proper handling of catalog err cond w/os-token and os-endpoint

This fix allows proper keystone catalog error msg to spew to the
console as oppose to 'NoneType' object has no attribute
'has_service_catalog'.

Change-Id: I15ae5822a15500d137e79556b0dfaed233d9782c
Closes-Bug: #1239219
Closes-Bug: #1362630

commit_message:
Remove the alarmDefinitionId field in the Alarm JSON

It is redundant with the id in the AlarmDefinition object and the
CLI has been modified to no longer use it

Change-Id: Idd575ce8b4988e2958fdbcb5fcefdf15fc39957c

[{'created': '2014-10-22 02:56:25.000000000', 'message': "Bump version string to coincide with kilo

The tempest-2 tag has been pushed to mark the start of support for the
kilo release. This commit bumps the version to 3 to show the current

commit_message:
Bump version string to coincide with kilo release

The tempest-2 tag has been pushed to mark the start of support for the
kilo release. This commit bumps the version to 3 to show the current
working tag number. Tempest-3 when it is tagged after the kilo release
will mark support for icehouse, juno, kilo, and the 'L' release based
on the current stable maintenance schedule.

Change-Id: If401356d441ef3dc82a5b8069168c4dd71c8b3d8

commit_message:
Make full bash-completion

Also removed some unused code in cliutils
Now `rally bash-completion' prints out bash completion script
Added test for checking completion script is up-to-date

Change-Id: I7e89baf71313da45e264fe344ff69be0e93a96d1

commit_message:
Use oslo.serialization

Replace usage of deprecated jsonutils module from oslo-incubator
and use oslo.serialization instead.

A followup-patch will sync with oslo-incubator and remove
the jsonutils module from manila.

Partial-Bug: #1382189

Change-Id: Iafa5090fd0c960ae8e996229ea3352f890decc6c

driver.

commit_message:
Fix RedHat service provider conditional

Without this patch, params.pp conditionally uses 'RedHat' as a matching
condition to $::operatingsystem for two different cases, and will match
on the first case. This is a problem because it will prevent the proper
service provider from being assigned on RedHat operating systems with
major version < 7. This patch removes RedHat from the first case so that
RedHat operating systems will match on the second case and assign the
init service provider if the major version is < 7.

Change-Id: Id5c49cc11a4112c27621c72a7b2e6fcaf9da6aef
(cherry picked from commit 9a5a540738f887f87886ae4f9f52d5ade1b26bc7)

commit_message:
libvirt: use instance object for attach_volume

The compute manager uses a instance object here. Add support to the
driver.

Change-Id: I32bc269ce392f1e41f0ddb88b912a5a4bfb7bad8

commit_message:
Lock table in _try_generate_ip even if there's no free range

In _try_generate_ip if the pool is exhausted, the table won't be
locked since the query to get the first available range will
return None. Lock the table anyway to prevent cuncurrent operations
to rebuild the availability ranges.

Change-Id: I15e5800c6c1df2db4085b0942edc5f06f753e3a4
Closes-bug: #1364085

commit_message:
libvirt: use instance object for resume_state_on_host_boot

The compute manager uses a instance object here. Add support to the
driver.

Change-Id: I6f81a62bcc95f7616414a102f1c470bb621b7bca

subject: libvirt: treat suspend instance as an object

commit_message:
libvirt: treat suspend instance as an object

The suspend method receives an object in the compute manager. This
method now uses an object in the driver.

Change-Id: Iccbb70553259aa914303d4d48583644b50a2f142

commit_message:
VMWare: Remove unused exceptions

Nova exceptions UseLinkedCloneConfigurationFault and
VMwareDriverConfigurationException now is present in
oslo.vmware library, so remove it and replace all of
its usages by usages of exceptions from oslo.vmware

Change-Id: I692030cff49965fac2d8da1bb76580fe9a607b61

commit_message:
Validate tenant_id part of TempURL in clients

Rackspace Cloud Files uses a UUID for the tenant ID, so move the code that
validates that part of the TempURL to the client.

Change-Id: I996fdc4b4b66e110066353d3b22ea3dab0535a5d

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-18 11:52:49.000000000', 'message': 'Allow specifying the gateway_external_network by name

This change makes the l3_agent recipe lookup the ID of the network used
for the gateway external network by name.  For example, specify

node[openstack][network][l3][gateway_external_network_name] = public

and the recipe will lookup the network by name.  It will use
openstack-common/libraries/cli.rb network_uuid method, effectively
querying `neutron net-external-list`.

Change-Id: I5df6f9989df7b18121a8050835a192da9e1a762e

commit_message:
Allow specifying the gateway_external_network by name

This change makes the l3_agent recipe lookup the ID of the network used
for the gateway external network by name.  For example, specify

node[openstack][network][l3][gateway_external_network_name] = public

and the recipe will lookup the network by name.  It will use
openstack-common/libraries/cli.rb network_uuid method, effectively
querying `neutron net-external-list`.  The result is saved to
gateway_external_network_id and used on subsequent runs.

To have the recipe check the UUID again (e.g. to update it), reset the
_id attribute to nil.

Change-Id: I5df6f9989df7b18121a8050835a192da9e1a762e

commit_message:
Use oslo.utils

Change usage of modules that are deprecated in oslo-incubator.
Use the corresponding module from oslo.utils.

A followup patch will sync with oslo-incubator and remove the now
obsolete modules.

Change-Id: I4f949de57e333832dcc7c1e256ce82e2db0144cb
Partial-Bug: #1382189

commit_message:
Move tests into manilaclient package

tests/__init__.py implies a package in the global namespace called tests.
That's not what these are, they are tests in the manilaclient namespace.

Also moved unit tests to dir 'unit', it is done so because 'functional' tests
are expected to be added.

Change-Id: I801214b865e9cef8db7511f209dcf3c26b75d70f

commit_message:
Fix of wizard bindings handling, prevent overwrite user input

When apply bindings on wizard pane change, apply only current pane
fields, not the whole wizard.

Change-Id: Ic1117ebe8850bd05ed86c7e2852a21daaef45124
Closes-Bug: #1384082

commit_message:
Allow file_upload_temp_dir override

This adds the ability to overide the
file_upload_temp_dir setting in django
which is usually '/tmp' by default but
may not be appropriate for all installations

Change-Id: Idebae5e0ec2249868f5ce411a7f798a7584fa40a

commit_message:
Do not use yield_per when eager loading is used

In our case using yield_per ended with duplicated rows.
SQLAlchemy docs do not recommend using it when joinedload
or subqueryload are used. In version 1.0 SQLAlchemy will raise
Exception http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/changelog/migration_10.html#joined-subquery-eager-loading-explicitly-disallowed-with-yield-per

Closes-bug: 1382627
blueprint 100-nodes-support

Change-Id: I1d9f3c14cba55eda0a0c9176ac745ed28a84476c

DocImpact

commit_message:
Add notification for server group operations

Currently, there is no notification when create/update/delete
server groups, this caused some 3rd party client cannot know
when those operations are finished.

The fix was adding notifications for those operations.

DocImpact
The wiki page https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/SystemUsageData
needs to be updated once this patch was merged.

Change-Id: Ia1f4a6752668ddb73ebb8faf525b58a28d183754
Closes-Bug: #1343200
(cherry picked from commit daf278c0c8b6cc917b84f514fec65758adf17028)

commit_message:
Run lint and syntax stackforge/puppet-* checks on trusty

Puppet module lint and syntax tests should also be run on trusty along
with unit tests. This patch adds lint and syntax tests to the regex to
skip assigning stable/icehouse branch tests to trusty nodes.

Change-Id: Id7f091678f0140f0d4feb9c317d653ac79b43d58

commit_message:
fix variable substitution when reporting NSX controller endpoint

- correctly substitute variable which contain NSX controller endpoint
  value
- report correct provider name in debug message of `rrpm' package
  provider, right now it misleads reader

Change-Id: I325ba8ef271cc54ed9a48d6fb0b3b1afcbd98c10
Closes-bug: #1380991

commit_message:
Nailgun plugins support

Basic version

Not solved issues:
- raise or ignore if plugin tasks fail;
- puppet runs using puppet or shell agent.

Change-Id: I1af308ff802fd7911f617168624f994dd69c563b
Implements: blueprint cinder-neutron-plugins-in-fuel

commit_message:
Don't automatically start and stop the topology

Let the subclasses control when the topology is created
and torn down

Change-Id: I972af67c6fb3602404e2c2d0237b1646e87aca55

http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec10.html

"10.4.10 409 Conflict

The request could not be completed due to a conflict with the current state of the resource. This code is only allowed in situations where it is expected that the user might be able to resolve the conflict and resubmit the request."

See the second sentence:

This code is only allowed in situations where it is expected that the user might be able to resolve the conflict and resubmit the request.

----

What you are looking for is probably:

10.4.4 403 Forbidden

The server understood the request, but is refusing to fulfill it. Authorization will not help and the request SHOULD NOT be repeated. revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-10 13:10:35.000000000', 'message': "Fix parent backup state validation

Reasons:
 - there's no parent backup checks at  incremental
   backup creation step, so, users are allowed to attempt to create
   incremental backup with FAILED parent.

Changes:
 - adding validation step that checks parent backup
   state and raises exception if it's FAILED.

Behaviour:
 - from client side it'll look like BadRequest with appropriate message:
   - Parent backup: %(backup_id)s is in FAILED state.

Change-Id: Ib52dd77d9d3e16d429d1cc7af37f55d2a80bc442
Closes-Bug: #1340163

"}, {'created': '2014-07-18 12:41:53.000000000', 'message': "Fix parent backup state validation

Reasons:
 - there's no parent backup checks at  incremental
   backup creation step, so, users are allowed to attempt to create
   incremental backup with FAILED parent.

Changes:
 - adding validation step that checks parent backup
   state and raises exception if it's FAILED;
 - parent validation was moved to speed up
   failing if backup is FAILED;
 - unit/int tests proposed.

Behaviour:
 - server will raise HTTP Conflict(409)
   if parent backup is in FAILED state.

Change-Id: Ib52dd77d9d3e16d429d1cc7af37f55d2a80bc442
Closes-Bug: #1340163

commit_message:
Fix parent backup state validation

Reasons:
 - there's no parent backup checks at  incremental
   backup creation step, so, users are allowed to attempt to create
   incremental backup with FAILED parent.

Changes:
 - adding validation step that checks parent backup
   state and raises exception if it's FAILED;
 - parent validation was moved to speed up
   failing if backup is FAILED;
 - unit/int tests proposed.

Behaviour:
 - server will raise ParentBackupFailedError;
 - from user perspective error will be interpreted
   as HTTP Forbidden(403) according to RFC 2616.

Change-Id: Ib52dd77d9d3e16d429d1cc7af37f55d2a80bc442
Closes-Bug: #1340163

commit_message:
Fix backup state check while restoring an instance

Reasons:
 - Trove API service checks backup only for NEW/BUILDING state,
   FAILED state also significant since users are not able to
   restore an instance from FAILED backup.

Changes:
 - adding 'is_failed' property to DBBackup object;
 - adding status validation at restoring;
 - fake int-tests proposed.

Behaviour:
 - server side raises HTTP Conflict(409) when attempting
   to restore an instance from backup that is still running or failed.

Change-Id: Ie2d92c16b98b0b941fb18a2cfa08fa3817f7ed74
Closes-Bug: #1338996

commit_message:
Wait also for keystone-2 backend for nova floating ips

Sometimes, keystone admin backend is not ready and this
leads to 504 errors during floating IP creation

This commit adds additional waiting exec.

Change-Id: Ia5d2b15b4b68b5692bb04103d62abc0f840232f0
Closes-bug: #1381982

commit_message:
Sync latest strutils from oslo-incubator for mask_password fix

This sync pulls in:
   1131b56 Enable mask_password to handle byte code strings

This is the only update since the last sync:
   beca4db Sync latest strutils from oslo-incubator

This is needed to fix a delete volume failure when processutils
calls mask_password with a byte code string.

Change-Id: Ie8a8c8e26abc0e387830bc9246e9a44913ae9b24
Closes-bug: #1368527
(cherry picked from commit cb5bcca025f9a34ecb9bc72b8fe570e6a63e442d)

commit_message:
allow for NON_STANDARD_REQS override

there are non integrated projects in openstack that use devstack framework
for running jobs. They need a lever in their jobs to tell the infrastructure
that we won't enforce global-requirements strict compliance on them. We'll
still generate a warning so that they know they are using requirements
outside of OpenStack's accepted list, but it will be non fatal.

See Sean's original patch to update.py in requirements repo:
Id90547e2fb0a5736385c9f31ba386e7c2e0616df

We need this to support specifically projects like nova-docker that
need some extra libraries (docker-py) but are not allowed to add these
libraries to global requirements since they are stackforge projects.

Change-Id: I70c6bc0c5324672bf910bb9278fdb33239d12736

Adding new scenarious for Heat

Previously all scenarious use only empty template. New scenarious use
templates with neutron and cinder resources.

Change-Id: I9bb349835ba3355902fb116980e241e3b77c9e49

commit_message:
Changing tests to accurately expect page elements

After some recent UI changes, the "show/hide full
configuration" links are now buttons rather than <a>
tags.  Also adjusting the field-filter box to use CSS
input.field-filter.

Change-Id: Ib4e3e4fa5faf1e400f6fdc43952405b14d1a871d
Closes-Bug:  #1383833

    policy_path => '/etc/neutron/policy.json',
    policies    => {...}
  }

  class { '::neutron::server': }

This solution also allows future API services to include neutron::policy from their manifests without risking having resource duplicates unlike with the class { 'neutron::policy': } syntax which would have to be used in neutron::server. This is a valid use case for Heat which has more than one API service.

For Hiera users:

  class { '::neutron::server': }
  # or
  include ::neutron::server

And then manage policies in Hiera:

  neutron::policy::policy_path: /etc/neutron/policy.json
  neutron::policy::policies:
    neutron-context_is_admin:
      context_is_admin: 'true'
    neutron-default:
      default: 'rule:admin_or_owner'"}, {'account_id': 3153, 'date': '2014-10-22 12:54:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

commit_message:
policy.json: Allow one to manage them from the puppet module

This commit allow a deployer to manage the policies via this module
It relies on augeas to change only the policy needed. The init takes
a hash of policies and apply them.

Change-Id: Iea6e7dccc2332045a2ebe191981538d045918f46

commit_message:
Reference git.o.o DevStack repo rather than GitHub

In docs, use git.o.o URLs rather than GitHub URLs for the DevStack repo,
and don't mention GitHub when git.o.o is more appropriate.
Also, replaced GitHub logo with Git logo in quickstart.png.

[{'created': '2014-08-20 20:43:50.000000000', 'message': 'Update contributing.rst to include guidelines on Code Review

An important part of contributing to the Trove project is to review
changes proposed by others. To reflect the value of this activity, and
provide some guidelines on how the Trove project would like reviews to
be conducted, I have updated the contributing.rst file with a summary
of some conversations at the mid-cycle meetup.

The intent is that reviews of this proposed change will be a
discussion not only of the summary that I have attempted to capture,
but also of the change(s) being proposed.

I've opted to provide only rough guidelines and not provide exhaustive
examples of "good" and "bad" reviews (the format used by, for example,
the commit message guidelines) because the intent is not to create
rigid and cumbersome process but rather to provide guidelines that
reflect the desired purpose of the review process.

It is acceptable to -1 this change if you find typographical errors,
or have suggestions on the formatting of the document ;)

Change-Id: I09432c335282c17974cb62b6f77cd00ebcdda21f

commit_message:
Update contributing.rst to include guidelines on Code Review

An important part of contributing to the Trove project is to review
changes proposed by others. To reflect the value of this activity, and
provide some guidelines on how the Trove project would like reviews to
be conducted, I have updated the contributing.rst file with a summary
of some conversations at the mid-cycle meetup.

The intent is that reviews of this proposed change will be a
discussion not only of the summary that I have attempted to capture,
but also of the change(s) being proposed.

I've opted to provide only rough guidelines and not provide exhaustive
examples of "good" and "bad" reviews (the format used by, for example,
the commit message guidelines) because the intent is not to create
rigid and cumbersome process but rather to provide guidelines that
reflect the desired purpose of the review process.

It is acceptable to -1 this change if you find typographical errors,
or have suggestions on the formatting of the document ;)

Change-Id: I09432c335282c17974cb62b6f77cd00ebcdda21f

commit_message:
Instance-Delete Should Stop the Database First

on instance-delete, the database should be stopped before deleting
the nova compute.

Closes-Bug #1381174

Change-Id: I94c2fa08be7faac37e1ac0a4460ad61f1f7ef164

commit_message:
Use EUI64 for IPv6 SLAAC when subnet is specified

This commit uses EUI64 for SLAAC and stateless IPv6 address
when subnet id in fixed_ip is specified.

After this patch, all the ports created on a subnet which has
ipv6_address_mod=slaac or ipv6_address_mod=dhcpv6-stateless
will use EUI64 as the address.
This patch also checks if fixed IP address is specified
for a IPv6 subnet with address mode slaac or dhcpv6-stateless
during creating or updating a port. If yes, raise InvalidInput
error to stop the port creation or update.

Remove unit test test_generated_duplicate_ip_ipv6 because
fixed_ip should not be specified for a slaac subnet.

Change-Id: Ie481cfb2f4313baf44bf1a838ebda374a5c74c6a
Closes-Bug: 1330826
(cherry picked from commit 3ba06618f79fed899188aac87a8694b3344ee995)

commit_message:
Improve monitoring in neutron-agent-dhcp OCF

* Added OCF_RESKEY_amqp_server_port parameter to neoutron-agent-dhcp OCF
  script
* Monitoring function monitors the connections to AMQP. Pacemaker will
  restart the service in case of problems with AMQP.

Change-Id: I5ee58d8268ae0d41322b53768b13ef2eb6522ead
Implements: bp/pacemaker-improvements

commit_message:
Revert "Ported repository installation from puppet-openstack"

This reverts commit b0b83dbf4507db36220f9c04c68e4788109b1c4b.

Repo management should be covered by the following spec:
extras-repository-refactor

Instead of the old puppet-openstack style
